[Episode 16]

15
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,688
Sis,

16
00:01:48,319 --> 00:01:50,359
my class was prolonged again.

17
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:52,079
No worries.

18
00:01:52,079 --> 00:01:54,380
I heard from Aunt that you've finally
proven your innocence

19
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,680
and that you're going back
to Markus. That's good.

20
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:05,359
Does Chen Mobai not want you to leave?

21
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:10,159
No, he didn't say that.

22
00:02:11,439 --> 00:02:14,199
So, do you not want to go back to Markus?

23
00:02:14,879 --> 00:02:15,904
Is it that?

24
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:25,759
Then why do you still look so worried?

25
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,479
Maybe I feel a bit down
for losing the competition.

26
00:02:35,879 --> 00:02:37,920
A game loss wouldn't make you feel like this

27
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,280
unless you think
that you are the reason he lost.

28
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:48,680
You can't hide any
emotional issues from my keen eye.

29
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:53,420
When two people start to get along,

30
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:55,800
there will surely be problems.

31
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,840
In our relationship,

32
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:07,919
indeed, there seems to be a certain paradox.

33
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,800
We both care about each other a lot,

34
00:03:14,479 --> 00:03:16,239
which is exactly the reason

35
00:03:16,239 --> 00:03:18,439
why we've become hesitant and restricted.

36
00:03:25,599 --> 00:03:27,159
What kind of logic is this?

37
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:39,479
Having feelings for someone
will naturally make you vulnerable.

38
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,620
If you want to resolve this,
you can use your subjective initiative.

39
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:44,879
Subjective initiative?

40
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,248
For example,

41
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,700
last time I wanted to invite Yuan Ye

42
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,960
to watch Chen Mobai's competition.

43
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,520
So I made a bet with myself.

44
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,860
I wagered on whether I would hit a wrong note

45
00:04:00,860 --> 00:04:02,039
in the next piano competition.

46
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:03,776
If I do,

47
00:04:04,599 --> 00:04:05,664
then forget it.

48
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,479
But if I play it right,

49
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,319
no matter whether he rejects me or not,

50
00:04:10,319 --> 00:04:12,000
I will take the initiative to ask him out.

51
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,864
And then?

52
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:20,060
Then, to play every note right,

53
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:22,020
I played it for like hundreds of times.

54
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:24,040
I almost wore out my fingernails.

55
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:29,840
So when you care about someone,

56
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,040
it's impossible for you
to not be affected by that at all.

57
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,080
But you need to see

58
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,000
if that influence is positive.

59
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,220
If after your efforts,

60
00:04:39,220 --> 00:04:41,820
both of you can develop in a good direction,

61
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:43,120
then there is no problem.

62
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,680
I must find a solution.

63
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,759
Otherwise, we will be stuck in place.

64
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:56,079
No matter how hard we hit the gas pedal,

65
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:58,279
we may not be able to move forward anymore.

66
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:15,584
So what are you really thinking?

67
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:17,800
Do you also accept this paradox

68
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,860
and think it's unsolvable?

69
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:20,920
Of course not.

70
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,728
Although theoretically,

71
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,759
I don't understand as much as she does,

72
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:32,480
I know what to do.

73
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,480
So have you decided what to do?

74
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,680
Starting with Linhai,

75
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,256
I have to win

76
00:05:41,639 --> 00:05:42,839
the upcoming competitions.

77
00:05:44,439 --> 00:05:45,472
I'm going to prove to her

78
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:48,600
that the paradox doesn't exist.

79
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,040
Actually,

80
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:57,480
everything you just said

81
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,439
is all judging what's best for her

82
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,199
from your perspective.

83
00:06:05,079 --> 00:06:08,160
You two are both the kind of people

84
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,839
who prefer to take ten actions for each other

85
00:06:09,839 --> 00:06:11,160
rather than say one word.

86
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,240
All right, it's getting late.

87
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,216
Get some rest.

88
00:07:00,068 --> 00:07:03,904
[For you, I made a bet with myself]

89
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:09,079
With this new model,

90
00:07:09,079 --> 00:07:10,336
as long as the issue of the airfoil

91
00:07:10,336 --> 00:07:12,279
and aerodynamic characteristics are cleared,

92
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,800
I can make a breakthrough.

93
00:07:36,199 --> 00:07:37,216
You're up.

94
00:07:39,399 --> 00:07:40,839
I'm taking you somewhere.

95
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,879
Where are we going?

96
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:42,976
You'll know once we're there.

97
00:08:10,176 --> 00:08:11,264
How about it?

98
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,879
Does it feel like a hidden Arcadia?

99
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:18,160
This is a beautiful place.

100
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:42,679
In theory, it's hard to simulate
steady wind in the outdoors,

101
00:08:43,519 --> 00:08:46,639
but here I can see the wind.

102
00:08:47,879 --> 00:08:50,279
It's flowing and changing.

103
00:09:02,679 --> 00:09:03,744
How's it going?

104
00:09:04,639 --> 00:09:06,399
I don't have a perfect solution yet,

105
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,720
but I've got a rough idea.

106
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,919
If you have got a rough idea,

107
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,639
can I make a little request?

108
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:17,639
What request?

109
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:21,480
I brought you here today to relax,

110
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,960
so I'm confiscating this notebook for now.

111
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:27,500
Wipe out all the programs

112
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:31,919
that have been taking up your memory recently.

113
00:09:31,919 --> 00:09:34,279
Give the brain that's been
running for too long a break,

114
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:35,968
all right?

