00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,200
we will turn the tables in this game.

125
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,120
Can this solve their paradox?

126
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:25,000
Why are you still talking about that paradox?

127
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:29,200
I'm just thinking about what's best for them.

128
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,159
I've said it earlier.

129
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,240
The fundamental problem with them
is that they're not suitable for each other.

130
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,320
If they insist on being together,

131
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,639
it would be troublesome for both of them.

132
00:10:39,399 --> 00:10:41,479
Even if you're right about that,

133
00:10:41,479 --> 00:10:44,399
Chen Mobai is truly worried
about Shen Xi's doubts.

134
00:10:44,399 --> 00:10:47,360
Putting aside the fact
that I'm the team manager,

135
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,820
and from the position of a friend,

136
00:10:48,820 --> 00:10:51,320
doesn't this clearly prove
that they care about each other

137
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:52,919
and like each other?

138
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,800
As long as there's love,
no difficulty is insurmountable.

139
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,760
Since there are so many
difficulties to overcome,

140
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,799
why be together?

141
00:11:01,559 --> 00:11:02,656
Isn't it tiring?

142
00:11:03,559 --> 00:11:05,360
That's normal people's romantic relationships.

143
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,520
It's mundane. Mundane as can be.

144
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:12,159
It might be, but that's love.

145
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:20,719
Let me tell you about the bliss
of us mundane people,

146
00:11:20,719 --> 00:11:22,279
which is,

147
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:24,320
when a couple both like spicy food,

148
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:27,039
they would order a mouth-numbing,
spicy boiled fish with pickles in a restaurant.

149
00:11:27,919 --> 00:11:28,928
And on a Tuesday,

150
00:11:29,799 --> 00:11:32,360
we buy discounted movie tickets.

151
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:35,080
Also, if you piss me off today,

152
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,860
regardless of the passing crowds around,

153
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:38,560
I will still argue with you,

154
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,679
without fearing you'd leave me over it.

155
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,559
And when you know I was in a queue

156
00:11:46,559 --> 00:11:48,360
for three hours to buy this ice cream,

157
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,440
you would enjoy it more.

158
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,632
Zhao Yingning,

159
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,879
I like you.

160
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:07,080
Will you marry me?

161
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:13,219
Why don't you try to let yourself go
in public once in a while?

162
00:12:13,219 --> 00:12:14,304
It's exhilarating.

163
00:12:15,519 --> 00:12:18,480
If you don't say yes, I won't get up.

164
00:12:24,159 --> 00:12:25,280
Are you crazy?

165
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:27,456
Good job, beauty!

166
00:12:28,639 --> 00:12:29,879
Why are you walking so fast?

167
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,960
I was just joking with you.

168
00:12:34,559 --> 00:12:35,799
How was it?

169
00:12:35,799 --> 00:12:38,759
Wasn't it exhilarating to be impulsive

170
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,512
once in a while?

171
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:48,300
Then, how about I take you to try

172
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,720
a mouth-numbing, spicy boiled fish

173
00:12:50,399 --> 00:12:52,799
and let you experience
the bliss of ordinary people?

174
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,384
It's so beautiful.

175
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,759
In the city, we can't see the stars.

176
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,879
The stars are so far away from us.

177
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,960
Their light was emitted
tens of thousands of years ago.

178
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:13,696
Tens of thousands of years?

179
00:13:15,679 --> 00:13:18,320
Does it take that long for a beam of light
to reach Earth?

180
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,639
To emit light and to be seen

181
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,080
might be the dream of a star.

182
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,679
Now that we've seen it,

183
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:28,799
its dream has come true.

184
00:13:30,279 --> 00:13:31,360
Dreams feel so distant.

185
00:13:37,279 --> 00:13:39,879
What about you, what's your dream?

186
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,679
To be a top-tier engineer?

187
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:03,039
I didn't seem to have any dreams as a child.

188
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,376
Instead, my older brother

189
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,159
had a clear goal.

190
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,848
He wanted to get into Formula B, and Formula A,

191
00:14:11,519 --> 00:14:12,919
up to the Super Grand Prix.

192
00:14:15,559 --> 00:14:17,600
I guess I just followed his path

193
00:14:18,679 --> 00:14:20,159
and ended up here today.

194
00:14:23,159 --> 00:14:25,000
I still remember the first time I saw him race.

195
00:14:25,879 --> 00:14:26,912
I was so curious.

196
00:14:27,519 --> 00:14:29,399
Why was the Aerodynamics kit so complicated,

197
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:32,360
and why did the rear diffuser
have to be made so large?

198
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:35,200
So I studied a bit,

199
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,208
and then,

200
00:14:39,679 --> 00:14:41,519
I got into TU Germany

201
00:14:42,639 --> 00:14:45,200
before I joined Markus.

202
00:14:48,559 --> 00:14:50,639
I feel like I've heard
the story of a genius girl.

203
00:14:54,039 --> 00:14:55,136
Not really.

204
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,200
It sounded easy,

205
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,519
but there had been many years in between.

206
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,600
What happened later?

207
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,320
Later, I found out

208
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:15,279
that racing seems to be more
than just a sports event,

209
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,840
but an industry chain,

210
00:15:19,679 --> 00:15:21,679
a high-tech industry.

211
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,519
The West has been ahead of us
by many, many years,

212
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:31,440
and it's very difficult to get
into the core of this circle.

213
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,440
For a girl to live
in such a hardcore environment,

214
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,600
to challenge, and to strive,

215
00:15:41,399 --> 00:15:42,464
it must be very hard, right?

216
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,784
Not really.

217
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,120
The environment is fair after all.

218
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,039
They've been ahead of us for so many years,

219
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,759
so we just have to adapt and learn first.

220
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,024
I still remember

221
00:16:06,039 --> 00:16:08,600
the day Wings of Wind was developed.

222
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,344
My brother and I,

223
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,264
and Shaoqian…

224
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,719
Girl, now I can finally say,

225
00:16:29,719 --> 00:16:31,279
the dream is right ahead of us.

226
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:34,799
I believe that in the near future,

227
00:16:35,759 --> 00:16:36,960
be it engineers

228
00:16:37,639 --> 00:16:38,720
or racing drivers,

229
00:16:39,679 --> 00:16:41,320
none of us will remain an anomaly.

230
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:47,519
Actually, the Super Grand Prix

231
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,440
is where you belong.

232
00:16:50,279 --> 00:16:51,360
I will go back,

233
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,159
but not alone.

234
00:16:55,879 --> 00:16:56,960
It will be you and I,

235
00:16:58,639 --> 00:17:00,519
along with our entire team.

236
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,840
This is my current dream.

237
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,680
Although I don't know

238
00:17:09,519 --> 00:17:11,839
how far off the day my brother mentioned is,

239
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,620
and we may still have to go through

240
00:17:16,620 --> 00:17:18,980
more technical difficulties
and psychological challenges,

241
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:21,319
I look forward to the day

242
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:24,359
when the Super Grand Prix
changes because of us.

243
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,248
It will.

244
00:17:33,664 --> 00:17:34,759
You will surely become

245
00:17:34,759 --> 00:17:35,920
a remarkable engineer.

246
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,319
Your dream will surely come true.

247
00:17:39,839 --> 00:17:41,799
Our dream will also come true.

248
00:17:44,079 --> 00:17:45,152
I've always believed

249
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:47,240
that as long as we are together,

250
00:17:48,079 --> 00:17:49,519
there are no hurdles we can't overcome.

251
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:52,680
There is no end we can't reach.

252
00:17:54,279 --> 00:17:55,296
It's been this way,

253
00:17:56,759 --> 00:17:57,920
and it always will be.

